- Coding convention
private method/functions  name_()  , so that it's easy to search for '_('
private var  _name



if a function returns an iterable object, e.g., list, then must return that object, never return None,  e.g,. return [1,2], [], {1:'on'}, {}, etc

For a compute function, i.e., does not return any real typed object, then use "return" instead of "return None"


- Requirements
run the check_requirements.py script to check
  






useful script

sage: sdir = "../invgen/Traces/NLA_ctr/"
# exec trace generation scripts (i.e. .sh)
sage: cmds = ["sh {} > {}.tcs".format(f,f[:f.find('.sh')]) for f in os.listdir(sdir) if f.endswith('.sh')]
sage: for cmd in cms: print(cmd); vcmd(cmd)

# run splitfile (preprocess traces)
sage:  _ = [ReadFile.split_files(os.path.join(sdir,f)) for f in os.listdir(sdir) if f.endswith('.tcs')]
 
